CLOSEThe Maricopa County jail population has decreased and fewer people are being booked, all as part of efforts to prevent the spread of the coronavirus, Sheriff Paul Penzone announced Thursday.
Citing restaurant violators, driversPenzone said his deputies have cited at least one restaurant for violating Gov.
Doug Ducey's orders to only offer takeout or delivery service.
The deputies cited the restaurant only after being called more than once to the business, Penzone said.
People or business owners violating Ducey's orders can be cited for a class-one misdemeanor and fined up to $2,500.